### 1. Werbungskosten – income-related expenses (§ 9 EStG)

| What the law calls it                            | Typical examples                                                        | How much you may deduct in 2025                                                                                  |
|--------------------------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Arbeitnehmer-Pauschbetrag (lump sum)             | Automatically granted to every employee                                  | € 1 230 without receipts                                                                                         |
| Entfernungspauschale (commuting allowance)       | Daily trip between home and first workplace, any transport mode          | € 0.30 / km for the first 20 km, € 0.38 / km from kilometre 21; normally no cap for motorists, otherwise € 4 500 cap |
| Home-office “Tagespauschale”                     | Working ≥ 50 % of the day at home                                        | € 6 per day, max € 1 260 (210 days) per year                                                                     |
| Work equipment & job supplies                    | Laptop, tools, professional books                                        | 100 % if cost ≤ € 1 000 net; otherwise over useful life; mixed use must be split                                |
| Travel & training costs                          | Business trips, second degree, language course needed for the job        | Actual costs incl. per-diem meal rates                                                                           |
| Double household (“doppelte Haushaltsführung”)   | Second flat near work                                                    | Rent + utilities up to € 1 000 per month + weekly trips home                                                     |

**Effect:** Reduces your taxable income directly.

