### 3. Sonderausgaben – special expenses (§ 10 – § 10d EStG)

| Typical item                                       | Deductible share / annual cap 2025                                                       |
|---------------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Retirement (Basisrente + statutory pension)       | 100 % up to € 29 344 single / € 58 688 married                                            |
| Basic health & long-term-care insurance           | 100 % of the “Basistarif”; extras (dentist, private ward) not deductible                 |
| Child-care costs (children < 14)                  | 80 % of expenses up to € 6 000 → € 4 800 max per child from 2025                          |
| School fees (Privatschule)                        | 30 % up to € 5 000 per child                                                              |
| Church tax & certain life/accident insurance      | 100 %                                                                                     |
| Donations & membership fees                       | Up to 20 % of total income or 4 ‰ of turnover + wages; excess can be carried forward     |
| Alimony to ex-spouse (Realsplitting)              | Up to € 13 805 + basic KV/PV premiums of the recipient                                   |
| Special-expense lump sum                          | € 36 single / € 72 married (if you claim nothing else)                                   |

**Effect:** Reduces taxable income.

